-- Ex-Coca-Cola aide found guilty in trade secrets case
-- 
-- Fri Feb 2, 2007 12:23pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/02/us-coke-tradesecrets-jury-idUSN3145954420070202

 

 ATLANTA  (Reuters) - A U.S. jury on Friday found a former Coca-Cola Co. ( KO.N ) executive assistant guilty of conspiring to steal trade secrets of the beverage giant and sell them to rival PepsiCo Inc.( PEP.N ) 


 The jury's verdict was read in U.S. District Court in Atlanta. Williams, a former aide to the director of global brands of Coca-Cola, could be sentenced to up to 10 years in prison.